job_descriptions:
For more than three decades, TCP Software (formerly known as TimeClock Plus) has provided premier workforce management solutions to millions of users every day. We meet the needs of our customers by providing innovative software and hardware designed to help administrators track employees, manage labor costs and reduce compliance risk. TCP’s software suite includes Time & Attendance, Leave Management, Document Management, Advanced and Dynamic Scheduling and more, all of which integrate with all major payroll systems as well as our extensive portfolio of time collection solutions. From private to public sector, organizations of all sizes rely on our easy-to-use solutions designed with one goal in mind: Empowering people to work better.

We have two product lines, TimeClock Plus software and Humanity software.

Humanity is a cloud-based workforce management software fueled by a commitment to innovation, iteration, and a customer-centric approach. Our platform brings together usability, smart design, and custom features to help managers and employees better organize and stay connected through our evolving suite of apps.

We are looking for an experienced Full Stack Developer to join our creative and talented team in Lahore.

Responsibilities
Resolving bugs and development of new features;
Development of internal tools;
API support;
Communication and cooperation with our Support and Development teams;
Communication with customers.
Requirements
Working experience with PHP, JavaScript, SQL;
Strong problem solving skills;
Excellent knowledge of English (both written and spoken);
Solid testing and debugging skills;
Strong communication and interpersonal skills;
Good organizational and time management skills;
Familiarity with JIRA;
Familiarity with Github.
Bonus Skills
Experience with Object Oriented PHP, Symfony, React, using REST services and MongoDB;
Previous experience working on SaaS projects;
Familiarity with Scrum methodology or other agile development processes.
Benefits
Competitive salary based on experience
PTO and Sick leaves
In-Patient Health insurance
Provident fund and EOBI
The work/life setup you need to be successful.
A creative, collaborative, supportive environment that gives you the autonomy to explore new ideas, grow your skillset, and create outstanding results
The chance to make a genuine impact on the company’s growth
Plenty of challenging work and the opportunity to stretch yourself
The opportunity to work with amazing talent in a fast-growing company that really values its team

